sql:
SELECT status_name
FROM survival_status
WHERE status_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
External Knowledge: 
Adults refer to passengers who are 18 years or older; 
Passenger classes include 1st, 2nd, and 3rd classes, each representing different levels of service and accommodations on the ship;
Survival rate is calculated as the percentage of passengers in a particular group who survived, out of the total number of passengers in that group.

sql:
SELECT AVG(fare) AS average_fare
FROM passengers
WHERE survived = 0;
